### Hadith 2:66

*Narrated Ibn Abbas:*

Once the Prophet (p.b.u.h) led the fear prayer and the people stood
behind him. He said Takbir (Allahu-Akbar) and the people said the same.
He bowed and some of them bowed. Then he prostrated and they also
prostrated. Then he stood for the second Raka and those who had prayed
the first Raka left and guarded their brothers. The second party joined
him and performed bowing and prostration with him. All the people were
in prayer but they were guarding one another during the prayer.

